  "steps": [
    {
      "id": "l4-family-theory",
      "type": "theory",
      "title": "Family members",
      "body": "# Die Familie — the family\n\n| German | English |\n|---|---|\n| **die Mutter** | the mother |\n| **der Vater** | the father |\n| **die Schwester** | the sister |\n| **der Bruder** | the brother |\n| **die Oma** | the grandma |\n| **der Opa** | the grandpa |\n| **die Eltern** | the parents *(plural)* |\n\nNotice the articles: female family members take **die**, male members take **der**. Remember that all nouns are written with a **capital letter**."
    },
    {
      "id": "l4-possessive-theory",
      "type": "theory",
      "title": "Saying \"my\"",
      "body": "# mein / meine — my\n\nThe word for *my* changes with the gender of the noun:\n\n- **mein** + masculine or neuter: *mein Bruder* (my brother), *mein Kind* (my child)\n- **meine** + feminine or plural: *meine Schwester* (my sister), *meine Eltern* (my parents)\n\nSo: **mein Vater** but **meine Mutter**."
    },
    {
      "id": "l4-ex-match-family",
      "type": "exercise",
      "title": "Match family members",
      "exercise": {
        "id": "l4-ex-match-family",
        "type": "matching",
        "prompt": "Match each German word with its English meaning.",
        "card_ids": ["de-die-mutter", "de-der-vater", "de-die-schwester", "de-der-bruder"],
        "pairs": [
          {"left": "die Mutter", "right": "the mother"},
          {"left": "der Vater", "right": "the father"},
          {"left": "die Schwester", "right": "the sister"},
          {"left": "der Bruder", "right": "the brother"}
        ],
        "direction": "target_to_source"
      }
    },
    {
